- Not true.

00:09:40.872 --> 00:09:43.750 position:50% align:center line:84%
The graffiti war was the proof
we needed to move forward.

00:09:43.833 --> 00:09:44.918 position:50% align:center line:84%
- [gasps]

00:09:45.293 --> 00:09:46.670 position:50% align:center line:84%
[shudders]

00:09:47.253 --> 00:09:48.922 position:50% align:center line:84%
- The gap's closing?

00:09:49.005 --> 00:09:52.217 position:50% align:center line:84%
- A powerful Go Vote movement
has gone viral,

00:09:52.300 --> 00:09:53.760 position:50% align:center line:84%
and the number
of DoRed supporters

00:09:53.843 --> 00:09:55.512 position:50% align:center line:84%
is increasing.

00:09:55.595 --> 00:09:57.681 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Preceding the eviction
of the Pylon Apartment,

00:09:57.764 --> 00:10:00.225 position:50% align:center line:84%
a neighborhood watch
has been set up in Shantytown.

00:10:00.308 --> 00:10:02.268 position:50% align:center line:84%
SARG doesn't have
the manpower.

00:10:02.352 --> 00:10:04.771 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Shall we ask the U.N.
for assistance?

00:10:04.854 --> 00:10:06.314 position:50% align:center line:84%
We should be able
to pressure them through

00:10:06.398 --> 00:10:08.149 position:50% align:center line:84%
the connections Mr. Howard has.

00:10:08.233 --> 00:10:10.151 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Do you honestly think we have
to go that far?

00:10:10.235 --> 00:10:11.361 position:50% align:center line:84%
- And much farther.

00:10:11.444 --> 00:10:12.946 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Consider the long term.

00:10:13.029 --> 00:10:16.825 position:50% align:center line:84%
It isn't wise to owe Mr. Howard
a single favor.

00:10:16.908 --> 00:10:18.576 position:50% align:center line:84%
- I see.

00:10:19.035 --> 00:10:20.912 position:50% align:center line:84%
Then how about
we take full advantage

00:10:20.995 --> 00:10:22.580 position:50% align:center line:84%
of what Hazard Cast can do?

00:10:22.664 --> 00:10:24.165 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Hmm.

00:10:24.249 --> 00:10:27.002 position:50% align:center line:84%
Felons don't have the right
to vote at present?

00:10:28.920 --> 00:10:30.046 position:50% align:center line:84%
All right.

00:10:30.505 --> 00:10:32.924 position:50% align:center line:84%
Forcibly evict Pylon Apartment.

00:10:33.717 --> 00:10:36.636 position:50% align:center line:84%
[dramatic music]

00:10:36.720 --> 00:10:43.601 position:50% align:center line:84%
♪ ♪

00:11:10.754 --> 00:11:12.464 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Kozue in danger!

00:11:18.011 --> 00:11:19.387 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Are they seriously going

00:11:19.471 --> 00:11:22.057 position:50% align:center line:84%
to make Shantytown
just disappear?

00:11:22.140 --> 00:11:26.186 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Everybody is acting based on
their own set of convictions.

00:11:26.269 --> 00:11:27.228 position:50% align:center line:84%
[exhales]

00:11:27.312 --> 00:11:28.730 position:50% align:center line:84%
It's a mess.

00:11:29.272 --> 00:11:30.231 position:50% align:center line:84%
- I know.

00:11:31.316 --> 00:11:32.609 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Help me!
[both gasping]

00:11:32.692 --> 00:11:34.861 position:50% align:center line:84%
- God dammit!
Stop, now!

00:11:34.944 --> 00:11:36.154 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Don't make
this harder on yourself!

00:11:36.237 --> 00:11:37.989 position:50% align:center line:84%
Calm down and stop!
- [breathing heavily]

00:11:38.073 --> 00:11:39.366 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Kozue?
- Whoa, hold on!

00:11:39.449 --> 00:11:40.617 position:50% align:center line:84%
Is that Kozue?
- [grunts]

00:11:40.700 --> 00:11:42.285 position:50% align:center line:84%
I'm heading down!
- All right.

00:11:46.706 --> 00:11:48.625 position:50% align:center line:84%
[tense music]

00:11:48.708 --> 00:11:50.669 position:50% align:center line:84%
- [breathing heavily]

00:11:50.752 --> 00:11:51.711 position:50% align:center line:84%
- [grunts]
- Hey!

00:11:51.795 --> 00:11:53.213 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Don't try to run!
- Let go of me!

00:11:53.296 --> 00:11:54.631 position:50% align:center line:84%
Let me go!
- Hold still, dammit!

00:11:54.714 --> 00:11:56.800 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Why would I ever listen
to SARG?

00:11:56.883 --> 00:12:00.261 position:50% align:center line:84%
- You spray painted a police car
which means you broke the law!

00:12:00.345 --> 00:12:02.639 position:50% align:center line:84%
- I don't care!
The law's totally screwed up!

00:12:02.722 --> 00:12:03.807 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Kaoru!

00:12:03.890 --> 00:12:05.100 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Uh, could you lend me
a hand here, Hana?

00:12:05.183 --> 00:12:06.017 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Look around.
- Huh?

00:12:12.399 --> 00:12:13.817 position:50% align:center line:84%
[camera shutter clicking]

00:12:13.900 --> 00:12:15.568 position:50% align:center line:84%
- This is really bad.

00:12:15.652 --> 00:12:17.404 position:50% align:center line:84%
- You're arresting such
a young girl!

00:12:17.946 --> 00:12:19.489 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Everyone, let's get 'em!

00:12:19.572 --> 00:12:22.450 position:50% align:center line:84%
[all shouting at once]

00:12:26.496 --> 00:12:27.664 position:50% align:center line:84%
- [grunts]

00:12:27.747 --> 00:12:29.708 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Wait!
- [grunts]

00:12:30.709 --> 00:12:31.710 position:50% align:center line:84%
- [groans]

00:12:31.793 --> 00:12:33.169 position:50% align:center line:84%
- What?
Shuta Aoi?

00:12:33.253 --> 00:12:34.671 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Take off!
- The crowd!

00:12:34.754 --> 00:12:36.715 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Just do it!
- Uh, Hana?

00:12:36.798 --> 00:12:38.591 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Hurry up and go!
- [groans]

00:12:38.675 --> 00:12:40.593 position:50% align:center line:84%
- They're getting away!
- Everyone calm down.

00:12:40.677 --> 00:12:42.512 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Whose side are you on, buddy?

00:12:42.595 --> 00:12:44.723 position:50% align:center line:84%
- It isn't about sides
or anything like that!

00:12:44.806 --> 00:12:46.599 position:50% align:center line:84%
- That's just lip service!
- [groans]

00:12:46.683 --> 00:12:48.435 position:50% align:center line:84%
- After them!
- [whimpers]

00:12:48.518 --> 00:12:51.646 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Yes, we will protect
our home, Shantytown!

00:12:51.730 --> 00:12:53.606 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Kick the SARG out!

00:12:53.690 --> 00:12:56.818 position:50% align:center line:84%
[all shouting]

00:12:58.695 --> 00:12:59.779 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Hey there, Shu.

00:13:01.448 --> 00:13:03.491 position:50% align:center line:84%
- You're not joining DoRed,
are you?

00:13:03.575 --> 00:13:05.076 position:50% align:center line:84%
It's dangerous.

00:13:05.160 --> 00:13:07.412 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Shu, you should help out DoRed
as well.

00:13:07.495 --> 00:13:09.414 position:50% align:center line:84%
Surveillance isn't the answer.

00:13:09.497 --> 00:13:11.249 position:50% align:center line:84%
Machines can't quantify justice.

00:13:11.332 --> 00:13:13.001 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Is that from DoRed?

00:13:13.084 --> 00:13:14.669 position:50% align:center line:84%
- You got a problem with it?

00:13:14.753 --> 00:13:16.338 position:50% align:center line:84%
You know, Shu,

00:13:16.421 --> 00:13:19.341 position:50% align:center line:84%
Kunai's grandma got evicted
from the home she loved so much!

00:13:19.424 --> 00:13:20.508 position:50% align:center line:84%
- [gasps]

00:13:20.592 --> 00:13:21.926 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Can you save her?

00:13:22.010 --> 00:13:23.345 position:50% align:center line:84%
You're just chasing
the problems right

00:13:23.428 --> 00:13:24.512 position:50% align:center line:84%
in front of you.

00:13:25.180 --> 00:13:27.390 position:50% align:center line:84%
Exactly whose hero are you, Shu?

00:13:27.891 --> 00:13:28.892 position:50% align:center line:84%
- [exhales]

00:13:30.018 --> 00:13:31.770 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Listen, I'm joining them.

00:13:33.438 --> 00:13:35.190 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Kozue, wait!

00:13:36.024 --> 00:13:37.233 position:50% align:center line:84%
Hey!

00:13:37.567 --> 00:13:38.568 position:50% align:center line:84%
[groans]

00:13:38.651 --> 00:13:41.529 position:50% align:center line:84%
[distant shouting]

00:13:51.623 --> 00:13:54.542 position:50% align:center line:84%
[dramatic music]

00:13:54.626 --> 00:13:55.794 position:50% align:center line:84%
♪ ♪

00:13:55.877 --> 00:13:56.920 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Huh?

00:13:57.003 --> 00:14:03.051 position:50% align:center line:84%
♪ ♪

00:14:03.134 --> 00:14:06.054 position:50% align:center line:84%
- [crying]

00:14:08.848 --> 00:14:11.351 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Asumi, it's getting
pretty dark.

00:14:11.434 --> 00:14:12.644 position:50% align:center line:84%
Let's go home.

00:14:12.727 --> 00:14:16.523 position:50% align:center line:84%
- My mom always told me
that if I just

00:14:16.606 --> 00:14:18.566 position:50% align:center line:84%
keep on doing the right thing,

00:14:18.650 --> 00:14:21.611 position:50% align:center line:84%
then someday good things
would happen back to me.

00:14:21.695 --> 00:14:24.781 position:50% align:center line:84%
But then my mom still died.

00:14:24.864 --> 00:14:26.866 position:50% align:center line:84%
Why did that happen to me?

00:14:27.367 --> 00:14:28.618 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Uh, it's because...

00:14:29.244 --> 00:14:32.163 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Was my momma lying to me?

00:14:32.247 --> 00:14:33.540 position:50% align:center line:84%
- No way!

00:14:33.623 --> 00:14:36.209 position:50% align:center line:84%
What Mrs. Kanae said
has got to be the truth!

00:14:36.292 --> 00:14:37.585 position:50% align:center line:84%
And besides...

00:14:38.211 --> 00:14:41.423 position:50% align:center line:84%
Besides, I'll make sure nothing
like this ever happens again!

00:14:42.090 --> 00:14:43.091 position:50% align:center line:84%
For you...

00:14:44.592 --> 00:14:47.387 position:50% align:center line:84%
I will become the hero
of the 24th ward!

00:14:49.639 --> 00:14:51.933 position:50% align:center line:84%
- [gasps]

00:14:52.017 --> 00:14:53.018 position:50% align:center line:84%
'Kay.

00:14:56.855 --> 00:14:58.815 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Hero, my ass.

00:14:58.898 --> 00:15:00.692 position:50% align:center line:84%
The town is such
a mess right now,

00:15:00.775 --> 00:15:02.068 position:50% align:center line:84%
and yet I...

00:15:02.736 --> 00:15:05.780 position:50% align:center line:84%
I let myself get caught up
in my own feelings.

00:15:05.864 --> 00:15:08.324 position:50% align:center line:84%
I haven't though about
how other people feel,

00:15:08.408 --> 00:15:11.661 position:50% align:center line:84%
unlike our teachers and Asumi.

00:15:11.745 --> 00:15:12.746 position:50% align:center line:84%
[cell phone vibrating]

00:15:12.829 --> 00:15:14.456 position:50% align:center line:84%
[gasps]
[vibrating continues]

00:15:15.498 --> 00:15:16.916 position:50% align:center line:84%
From the hospital?

00:15:17.709 --> 00:15:19.127 position:50% align:center line:84%
Hello?

00:15:20.962 --> 00:15:23.423 position:50% align:center line:84%
- No!
If you go meet her...

00:15:23.506 --> 00:15:25.467 position:50% align:center line:84%
[beeping]
- Again?

00:15:25.550 --> 00:15:28.511 position:50% align:center line:84%
Have we figured out why all
these errors are happening?

00:15:29.137 --> 00:15:30.388 position:50% align:center line:84%
Sir?

00:15:31.139 --> 00:15:33.266 position:50% align:center line:84%
- We're currently working
on that problem.

00:15:33.350 --> 00:15:35.268 position:50% align:center line:84%
Give us a little bit
of time to adjust.

00:15:35.352 --> 00:15:37.312 position:50% align:center line:84%
I have an emergency.
I need to go to the hospital.

00:15:37.395 --> 00:15:39.147 position:50% align:center line:84%
[gasps]

00:15:39.230 --> 00:15:41.066 position:50% align:center line:84%
Shuta's a terrorist?

00:15:41.149 --> 00:15:43.443 position:50% align:center line:84%
Impossible.
That can't be.

00:15:44.652 --> 00:15:45.862 position:50% align:center line:84%
What is this, Asumi?

00:15:45.945 --> 00:15:48.865 position:50% align:center line:84%
[tense music]

00:15:48.948 --> 00:15:52.494 position:50% align:center line:84%
♪ ♪

00:15:52.577 --> 00:15:53.995 position:50% align:center line:84%
- What do you think?

00:15:54.079 --> 00:15:55.955 position:50% align:center line:84%
A good way
of influencing public opinion,

00:15:56.039 --> 00:15:57.123 position:50% align:center line:84%
wasn't it?

00:15:57.207 --> 00:15:59.668 position:50% align:center line:84%
[all shouting]

00:15:59.751 --> 00:16:02.504 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Well done.
And thanks to the momentum,

00:16:02.587 --> 00:16:04.631 position:50% align:center line:84%
DoRed has reclaimed its hideout.

00:16:04.714 --> 00:16:06.841 position:50% align:center line:84%
It's time we strike back.

00:16:06.925 --> 00:16:09.594 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Leave the broadcast
preparations to us.

00:16:10.220 --> 00:16:11.179 position:50% align:center line:84%
- [grunts]

00:16:11.262 --> 00:16:12.597 position:50% align:center line:84%
[exhales]

00:16:12.681 --> 00:16:16.810 position:50% align:center line:84%
Oh, how I've missed this couch.
Ah.

00:16:16.893 --> 00:16:18.770 position:50% align:center line:84%
- It's a bit lonely here
without you.

00:16:20.271 --> 00:16:22.190 position:50% align:center line:84%
- DoRed's headquarters.

00:16:22.899 --> 00:16:25.819 position:50% align:center line:84%
Kinako,
you are a member of DoRed.

00:16:25.902 --> 00:16:28.530 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Yeah, sorry I kept quiet
about it.

00:16:28.613 --> 00:16:31.908 position:50% align:center line:84%
- You finally up to talkin'
to me about this?

00:16:31.991 --> 00:16:34.452 position:50% align:center line:84%
- I guess there's no point
in hiding this from you now.

00:16:35.537 --> 00:16:37.622 position:50% align:center line:84%
- The Cornucopia blueprints?

00:16:38.206 --> 00:16:40.041 position:50% align:center line:84%
But it's not the public one.

00:16:40.125 --> 00:16:43.128 position:50% align:center line:84%
- This is the prototype
that Kanae developed.

00:16:43.712 --> 00:16:46.047 position:50% align:center line:84%
This is the heart
of the true KANAE System.

00:16:46.131 --> 00:16:47.424 position:50% align:center line:84%
- What do you mean?

00:16:48.049 --> 00:16:50.468 position:50% align:center line:84%
What the hell
is Gori Suido hiding?

00:16:53.471 --> 00:16:55.181 position:50% align:center line:84%
- I'm glad you're awake now.

00:16:55.807 --> 00:16:57.934 position:50% align:center line:84%
How are you feeling?
- Shuta.

00:16:58.351 --> 00:17:01.438 position:50% align:center line:84%
You're the savior who pulled
me off the trolley tracks?

00:17:01.521 --> 00:17:03.440 position:50% align:center line:84%
- So you do know after all.

00:17:04.065 --> 00:17:05.191 position:50% align:center line:84%
- [grunts]

00:17:05.817 --> 00:17:09.779 position:50% align:center line:84%
- I got a call from Asumi
so I picked it up,

00:17:09.863 --> 00:17:11.990 position:50% align:center line:84%
and a vision of the future
flooded through my mind.

00:17:12.073 --> 00:17:13.867 position:50% align:center line:84%
- That was an S.O.S.
from Miss Asumi.

00:17:13.950 --> 00:17:15.285 position:50% align:center line:84%
- [gasps]
Just like I thought!

00:17:15.368 --> 00:17:16.911 position:50% align:center line:84%
Asumi's still alive!
- No.

00:17:16.995 --> 00:17:18.997 position:50% align:center line:84%
She's not.
- Huh?

00:17:19.080 --> 00:17:21.416 position:50% align:center line:84%
But you just said the call
was from her.

00:17:22.208 --> 00:17:24.377 position:50% align:center line:84%
- The situation's complicated.

00:17:24.461 --> 00:17:27.005 position:50% align:center line:84%
I'll tell you everything
in a moment.

00:17:28.715 --> 00:17:31.676 position:50% align:center line:84%
The first thing you need
to understand

00:17:31.760 --> 00:17:33.762 position:50% align:center line:84%
is the KANAE System.

00:17:33.845 --> 00:17:36.014 position:50% align:center line:84%
The idea
was originally developed

00:17:36.097 --> 00:17:38.933 position:50% align:center line:84%
by Mrs. Kanae.
Currently, though,

00:17:39.017 --> 00:17:41.394 position:50% align:center line:84%
I am the KANAE System's
lead developer.

00:17:42.604 --> 00:17:44.564 position:50% align:center line:84%
After the first few months,

00:17:44.647 --> 00:17:47.609 position:50% align:center line:84%
development hit
a complete standstill.

00:17:47.692 --> 00:17:50.779 position:50% align:center line:84%
The original system designed
by Mrs. Kanae...

00:17:52.280 --> 00:17:54.115 position:50% align:center line:84%
Required a human brain

00:17:54.199 --> 00:17:56.368 position:50% align:center line:84%
as its entire
computational unit.

00:17:56.826 --> 00:17:58.328 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Huh?
- With the realization

00:17:58.411 --> 00:18:00.038 position:50% align:center line:84%
that it was inhumane,

00:18:00.121 --> 00:18:02.999 position:50% align:center line:84%
Mrs. Kanae abandoned
her research.

00:18:03.083 --> 00:18:06.503 position:50% align:center line:84%
However, Mr. Gori and I chose
to put our futures on

00:18:06.586 --> 00:18:08.088 position:50% align:center line:84%
the line for this project.

00:18:08.171 --> 00:18:11.257 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Oh, because Ms. Kanae...
- Yes.

00:18:11.341 --> 00:18:13.468 position:50% align:center line:84%
She should never have died
in such a way.

00:18:14.803 --> 00:18:17.430 position:50% align:center line:84%
We resumed our research,
but in the end,

00:18:17.514 --> 00:18:19.766 position:50% align:center line:84%
we could not create
a viable substitute.

00:18:19.849 --> 00:18:22.477 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Something to substitute
a brain?

00:18:22.560 --> 00:18:24.813 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Correct.
However,

00:18:24.896 --> 00:18:27.691 position:50% align:center line:84%
there was a turning point
in the halted research about

00:18:27.774 --> 00:18:29.067 position:50% align:center line:84%
a year and a half ago.

00:18:29.651 --> 00:18:32.070 position:50% align:center line:84%
The Takara
Elementary School fire.

00:18:32.153 --> 00:18:33.822 position:50% align:center line:84%
Do you understand?
- Huh?

00:18:33.905 --> 00:18:34.989 position:50% align:center line:84%
That means...

00:18:35.490 --> 00:18:37.826 position:50% align:center line:84%
- [grunts]
And after,

00:18:37.909 --> 00:18:41.413 position:50% align:center line:84%
Mr. Suido ordered me
to transplant Asumi into

00:18:41.496 --> 00:18:42.997 position:50% align:center line:84%
the system core.

00:18:43.081 --> 00:18:46.626 position:50% align:center line:84%
- You're telling me inside
the KANAE System...

00:18:47.085 --> 00:18:49.504 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Ms. Asumi's corpse
is being put to use.

00:18:49.587 --> 00:18:51.047 position:50% align:center line:84%
- [gasps]

00:18:51.131 --> 00:18:53.174 position:50% align:center line:84%
[tense music]

00:18:53.258 --> 00:18:55.552 position:50% align:center line:84%
No way.
You're kidding.

00:18:55.635 --> 00:18:57.220 position:50% align:center line:84%
But that is crazy!

00:18:57.303 --> 00:18:59.556 position:50% align:center line:84%
How come?
Why did you do that?

00:18:59.639 --> 00:19:02.142 position:50% align:center line:84%
- So we don't have
another tragedy.

00:19:02.225 --> 00:19:06.271 position:50% align:center line:84%
Mr. Suido decided to use
an inhumane system

00:19:06.354 --> 00:19:08.982 position:50% align:center line:84%
for the safety
of the 24th ward.

00:19:09.065 --> 00:19:12.068 position:50% align:center line:84%
- But you--
you've gone way too far!

00:19:12.152 --> 00:19:15.030 position:50% align:center line:84%
- The system
with its human transplant

00:19:15.113 --> 00:19:20.452 position:50% align:center line:84%
was operating so smoothly
as if blessed by an angel until

00:19:20.535 --> 00:19:24.122 position:50% align:center line:84%
the day you three received
a phone call from Miss Asumi.

00:19:24.456 --> 00:19:25.915 position:50% align:center line:84%
- That phone call.

00:19:25.999 --> 00:19:28.918 position:50% align:center line:84%
- The fact that the phone call
only sought help

00:19:29.002 --> 00:19:31.504 position:50% align:center line:84%
from Koki Suido,
Ran Akagi,

00:19:31.588 --> 00:19:34.299 position:50% align:center line:84%
and yourself gave me
a bad feeling.

00:19:35.133 --> 00:19:38.386 position:50% align:center line:84%
Without a doubt,
Asumi is biologically dead.

00:19:39.012 --> 00:19:42.057 position:50% align:center line:84%
But what if by connecting
her brain to a machine

00:19:42.140 --> 00:19:43.683 position:50% align:center line:84%
and running electricity
through it

00:19:43.767 --> 00:19:45.769 position:50% align:center line:84%
her consciousness
was reawakened?

00:19:45.852 --> 00:19:49.105 position:50% align:center line:84%
- SO the KANAE System brought
her back to life?

00:19:49.189 --> 00:19:50.440 position:50% align:center line:84%
- I don't know.

00:19:50.523 --> 00:19:52.275 position:50% align:center line:84%
Until we know for certain,

00:19:52.359 --> 00:19:55.028 position:50% align:center line:84%
I couldn't let this conscience
be erased as a bug,

00:19:55.111 --> 00:19:57.030 position:50% align:center line:84%
and that's why I arranged

00:19:57.113 --> 00:19:59.157 position:50% align:center line:84%
a fake hack into
the KANAE System.

00:19:59.240 --> 00:20:02.243 position:50% align:center line:84%
- So then Carneades was just a--

00:20:02.327 --> 00:20:04.788 position:50% align:center line:84%
- I used him to buy time.

00:20:05.413 --> 00:20:07.957 position:50% align:center line:84%
I placed a mapping sensor
at the Cornucopia

00:20:08.041 --> 00:20:09.250 position:50% align:center line:84%
and observed

00:20:09.334 --> 00:20:10.418 position:50% align:center line:84%
the electrical currents
throughout

00:20:10.502 --> 00:20:12.003 position:50% align:center line:84%
the ward.

00:20:12.087 --> 00:20:14.673 position:50% align:center line:84%
Typically, Asumi
is distributed all over

00:20:14.756 --> 00:20:17.967 position:50% align:center line:84%
the system and her presence
can't be perceived.

00:20:18.843 --> 00:20:21.888 position:50% align:center line:84%
But not when Hazard Cast deals
with certain people.

00:20:22.722 --> 00:20:25.266 position:50% align:center line:84%
If Asumi's acquaintances
are involved,

00:20:25.350 --> 00:20:27.102 position:50% align:center line:84%
the dispersed
consciousness becomes

00:20:27.185 --> 00:20:29.062 position:50% align:center line:84%
a single point of focus.

00:20:29.145 --> 00:20:33.149 position:50% align:center line:84%
- That means Asumi
was seeking us out for help

00:20:33.233 --> 00:20:35.276 position:50% align:center line:84%
in the moment she returned
to being herself?

00:20:35.360 --> 00:20:37.821 position:50% align:center line:84%
- The visions are screams.

00:20:37.904 --> 00:20:40.240 position:50% align:center line:84%
Asumi became part
of the KANAE System

00:20:40.323 --> 00:20:42.742 position:50% align:center line:84%
to help us but keeps
seeing nightmares

00:20:42.826 --> 00:20:45.328 position:50% align:center line:84%
of what may happen
in the 24th ward.

00:20:45.412 --> 00:20:47.080 position:50% align:center line:84%
When she knows that one
of the futures

00:20:47.163 --> 00:20:48.540 position:50% align:center line:84%
has to come true,

00:20:48.623 --> 00:20:51.084 position:50% align:center line:84%
she can't hold it in any longer,

00:20:51.167 --> 00:20:53.712 position:50% align:center line:84%
so Asumi wakes up and seeks help
from you three

00:20:53.795 --> 00:20:55.505 position:50% align:center line:84%
by presenting trolley dilemmas.

00:20:57.507 --> 00:21:00.218 position:50% align:center line:84%
- She was in agony.
Poor Asumi.

00:21:00.301 --> 00:21:02.595 position:50% align:center line:84%
She was turning to us three
for help.

00:21:03.304 --> 00:21:05.223 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Each time she calls for help,

00:21:05.306 --> 00:21:08.268 position:50% align:center line:84%
the KANAE System racks up
more bugs.

00:21:08.351 --> 00:21:10.687 position:50% align:center line:84%
I was afraid that
Miss Asumi's consciousness

00:21:10.770 --> 00:21:12.939 position:50% align:center line:84%
would soon race out of control,

00:21:13.023 --> 00:21:16.192 position:50% align:center line:84%
so I decided to put her
in eternal slumber.

00:21:16.860 --> 00:21:19.529 position:50% align:center line:84%
If I get enough data
through observation,

00:21:19.612 --> 00:21:22.699 position:50% align:center line:84%
I can forcefully disperse
her consciousness right before

00:21:22.782 --> 00:21:24.617 position:50% align:center line:84%
she wakes up from a nightmare.

00:21:24.701 --> 00:21:27.412 position:50% align:center line:84%
Theoretically,
that is possible to achieve.

00:21:27.495 --> 00:21:29.831 position:50% align:center line:84%
- But that doesn't change
the fact that she

00:21:29.914 --> 00:21:30.999 position:50% align:center line:84%
will keep suffering through

00:21:31.082 --> 00:21:33.001 position:50% align:center line:84%
these nightmares every time,
right?

00:21:33.084 --> 00:21:35.420 position:50% align:center line:84%
You would put Asumi through
that much agony?

00:21:35.503 --> 00:21:37.422 position:50% align:center line:84%
- I have no other way!
- [gasps]

00:21:38.214 --> 00:21:39.591 position:50% align:center line:84%
- [exhales]

00:21:40.300 --> 00:21:41.634 position:50% align:center line:84%
I'm so sorry.

00:21:42.177 --> 00:21:44.054 position:50% align:center line:84%
I know I'm ridiculous.

00:21:44.137 --> 00:21:46.514 position:50% align:center line:84%
Asumi has passed away.

00:21:46.598 --> 00:21:49.100 position:50% align:center line:84%
It's merely a digital residue
of her old thoughts.

00:21:49.184 --> 00:21:52.228 position:50% align:center line:84%
I know all that but still,
I can't--I don't--

00:21:52.771 --> 00:21:55.607 position:50% align:center line:84%
I don't know how--
how I could face Ms. Kanae

00:21:55.690 --> 00:21:57.317 position:50% align:center line:84%
if I've allowed Asumi...

00:21:57.400 --> 00:21:59.319 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Ms. Tsuzuragawa.

00:21:59.819 --> 00:22:02.947 position:50% align:center line:84%
- When I found out I was on
the tracks of destiny atop

00:22:03.031 --> 00:22:05.116 position:50% align:center line:84%
the Cornucopia during the storm,

00:22:05.200 --> 00:22:07.077 position:50% align:center line:84%
I'd already made up my mind.

00:22:07.827 --> 00:22:09.954 position:50% align:center line:84%
I had committed a mortal sin

00:22:10.038 --> 00:22:12.665 position:50% align:center line:84%
and I made Miss Asumi shoulder
the burden.

00:22:13.500 --> 00:22:17.420 position:50% align:center line:84%
Death was a punishment
which suited my terrible crime.

00:22:18.380 --> 00:22:21.466 position:50% align:center line:84%
But I was supposed
to die up there

00:22:21.549 --> 00:22:22.926 position:50% align:center line:84%
yet I'm still alive.

00:22:24.219 --> 00:22:26.304 position:50% align:center line:84%
It was only because
you saved me.

00:22:27.055 --> 00:22:29.391 position:50% align:center line:84%
Because you didn't give up
on hope.

00:22:29.474 --> 00:22:31.017 position:50% align:center line:84%
Because you're a hero.

00:22:31.101 --> 00:22:32.477 position:50% align:center line:84%
- [gasps]

00:22:32.560 --> 00:22:34.270 position:50% align:center line:84%
- I had always believed
that heroes

00:22:34.354 --> 00:22:35.980 position:50% align:center line:84%
were a bunch of nonsense.

00:22:36.815 --> 00:22:40.568 position:50% align:center line:84%
But from you I feel
there's something similar

00:22:40.652 --> 00:22:42.946 position:50% align:center line:84%
to Ms. Kanae and Miss Asumi.

00:22:43.029 --> 00:22:46.032 position:50% align:center line:84%
- [gasps]
I'm the same as the two of them?

00:22:46.116 --> 00:22:48.743 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Mr. Shuta,
tell me please.

00:22:48.827 --> 00:22:51.454 position:50% align:center line:84%
How would you go about saving
Ms. Asumi?

00:22:52.497 --> 00:22:53.581 position:50% align:center line:84%
[banging]

00:22:53.665 --> 00:22:55.125 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Okay.

00:22:55.208 --> 00:22:56.751 position:50% align:center line:84%
If it's like this,

00:22:56.835 --> 00:22:58.294 position:50% align:center line:84%
the KANAE System...

00:22:59.671 --> 00:23:02.590 position:50% align:center line:84%
Is 100% broken.

00:23:03.425 --> 00:23:06.011 position:50% align:center line:84%
- Asumi, I will allow you
to keep sleeping.

00:23:07.429 --> 00:23:09.639 position:50% align:center line:84%
I will build you
a swaying crib free

00:23:09.723 --> 00:23:11.016 position:50% align:center line:84%
of nightmares.

00:23:11.808 --> 00:23:15.645 position:50% align:center line:84%
There's no need for you
to be in agony at all.

